    <h2>How We Evaluated These Apps</h2>
    <p>Each app on this list was evaluated across six criteria: cost (including what the free tier actually provides), budgeting methodology, bank sync reliability, user interface quality, reporting and insights, and data privacy practices. We prioritized apps that have been on the market for at least two years, have a substantial user base, and receive regular updates. Flash-in-the-pan apps that might disappear next year were excluded because trusting your financial data to an unstable company creates unnecessary risk.</p>
    <p>The single most important factor is methodology alignment. A zero-based budgeting app will frustrate someone who prefers a spend-tracking approach, and vice versa. Before you look at features and pricing, decide which budgeting method resonates with you (see the methodology section below), then narrow your choices from there.</p>

